ussels South Charleroi Airport|Charleroi]], [[Li\u00e8ge Airport|Li\u00e8ge]], [[Lille Airport|Lille]], [[Ostend\u2013Bruges International Airport|Ostend/Bruges]]\n<!-- -->\n| [[TUI fly Deutschland]] | '''Seasonal:''' [[EuroAirport Basel\u2013Mulhouse\u2013Freiburg|Basel/Mulhouse]], [[Cologne Bonn Airport|Cologne/Bonn]], [[D\u00fcsseldorf Airport|D\u00fcsseldorf]], [[Frankfurt Airport|Frankfurt]], [[Hannover Airport|Hannover]], [[Munich Airport|Munich]], [[Nuremberg Airport|Nuremberg]], [[Paderborn Lippstadt Airport|Paderborn/Lippstadt]], [[Saarbr\u00fccken Airport|Saarbr\u00fccken]], [[Stuttgart Airport|Stuttgart]]\n<!-- -->\n| {{nowrap|[[TUI fly Netherlands]]}}| '''Seasonal:''' [[Amsterdam Airport Schiphol|Amsterdam]], [[Eindhoven Airport|Eindhoven]], [[Groningen Airport Eelde|Groningen]], [[Rotterdam The Hague Airport|Rotterdam]]\n<!-- -->\n| [[Ural Airlines]]| '''Seasonal charter:''' [[Koltsovo Airport|Yekaterinburg]]<ref name=\"Tez.ru\"/>\n<!-- -->\n| [[Volotea]] |[[Athens International Airport|Athens]] <br> '''Seasonal:''' [[Bari Karol Wojty\u0142a Airport|Bari]], [[Genoa Cristoforo Colombo Airport|Genoa]] (begins 8 July 2020),<ref>{{cite web |last1=Liu |first1=Jim |title=Volotea S20 network additions as of 10OCT19 |url=https://www.routesonline.com/news/38/airlineroute/286830/volotea-s20-network-additions-as-of-10oct19/ |website=Routesonline |accessdate=11 October 2019}}</ref> [[Lyon\u2013Saint-Exup\u00e9ry Airport|Lyon]] (begins 18 April 2020),<ref>https://www.volotea.com/en/flight-offers/lyon/heraklion-crete/?departureDate=2020-04-18&returnDate=2020-04-25&adults=1&childs=0&infants=0&jorney=oneway</ref> [[Marseille Provence Airport|Marseille]], [[Mykonos Airport|Mykonos]] (begins 29 May 2020), [[Naples International Airport|Naples]], [[Falcone\u2013Borsellino Airport|Palermo]], [[Thessaloniki Airport|Thessaloniki]] (begins 17 April 2020),<ref>https://www.voria.gr/article/i-volotea-archizi-ptisis-apo-thessaloniki-gia-dio-proorismous</ref> [[Venice Marco Polo Airport|Venice]], [[Verona Villafranca Airport|Verona]]\n<!-- -->\n| [[Vueling]] | '''Seasonal:''' [[Barcelona\u2013El Prat Airport|Barcelona]], [[Leonardo da Vinci\u2013Fiumicino Airport|Rome\u2013Fiumicino]]\n<!-- -->\n| [[Windrose Airlines]] | '''Seasonal charter:''' [[Boryspil International Airport|Kiev\u2013Boryspil]]<ref name=\"Tez.uk\">{{cite web|url=https://www.tez-tour.com/ru/kiev/avia-reference.html|title=Timetable|website=www.tez-tour.com}}</ref>\n<!-- -->\n| [[Wizz Air]] | '''Seasonal:''' [[Budapest Ferenc Liszt International Airport|Budapest]], [[David the Builder Kutaisi International Airport|Kutaisi]] (begins {{date|2020-7-3}})<ref name=\"Wizz_KUT_W20_Launch\">{{cite news |last1=Liu |first1=Jim |title=Wizz Air boosts Kutaisi network from Sep 2019 |url=https://www.routesonline.com/news/38/airlineroute/285429/wizz-air-boosts-kutaisi-network-from-sep-2019/ |accessdate=17 July 2019 |work=Routesonline |date=17 July 2019}}</ref>\n<!-- -->\n| [[Yakutia Airlines]] | '''Seasonal charter:''' [[Vnukovo International Airport|Moscow\u2013Vnukovo]]<ref name=\"Tez.ru\">{{cite web|url=https://www.tez-tour.com/avia-reference.html|title=Timetable|website=www.tez-tour.com}}</ref>\n<!-- -->\n}}\n\n==Statistics==\n\n===Traffic figures===\n'''Historical annual traffic statistics'''<ref name=HERSTAT>{{cite web |url=http://www.ypa.gr/userfiles/fa3cb89c-ac1a-4d4b-99ab-a34f011804e1/HERAKLEIO.xlsx|title=Statistical data of Iraklion airport \"N. Kazantzakis\" for the period 1994\u20132014 |accessdate=9 January 2016 |publisher=Hellenic Civilian Aviation Authority |format=XLS}}</ref>\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Year !! Flights !! Passengers !! Passengers Change (%)\n|-\n| 2001 || 39,290 || 5,046,726 || {{decrease}} 2.0\n|-\n| 2002 || 36,664 || 4,791,729 || {{decrease}} 5.1\n|-\n| 2003 || 39,523 || 4,833,507 || {{increase}} 0.9\n|-\n| 2004 || 38,170 || 4,712,508 || {{decrease}} 2,5\n|-\n| 2005 || 38,266 || 4,932,911 || {{increase}} 4.7\n|-\n| 2006 || 43,740 || 5,345,652 || {{incr